        "calculation": "1. Determine if the sign occupied by the planet in the D1 chart (or the sign from which the D60 is derived) is an odd sign (Aries, Gemini, Leo, Libra, Sagittarius, Aquarius) or an even sign (Taurus, Cancer, Virgo, Scorpio, Capricorn, Pisces). 2. Identify the specific Shashtyamsa number (1-60) the planet falls into. 3. Apply the following classification: If the sign is odd, Shashtyamsas 1, 2, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 15, 16, 30, 31, 32, 33, 34, 35, 39, 40, 42, 43, 44, 48, 51, 52, 59 are Krura (unpropitious), and the rest are Saumya (propitious). If the sign is even, the nature is reversed: the Shashtyamsas listed as Krura for odd signs become Saumya (propitious), and those listed as Saumya for odd signs become Krura (unpropitious).",
        "threshold": null,
        "comparison": null
      },
      "halt_on_failure": false,
      "impact_if_violated": "Incorrect assessment of a planet's subtle strength and auspiciousness in the D60, leading to flawed predictions regarding the deeper karmic implications and subtle results.",
      "impact_percentage": 60,
      "cancellation_conditions": [],
      "lagna_specific_rules": null,
      "classical_reference": "Phaladeepika Sloka 5",
      "chapter": null,
