        "condition": "When calculating the duration of Antardasas (Bhuktis) or further sub-divisions within any Dasa system.",
        "calculation": "The duration of an Antardasa is calculated by multiplying the years of the Mahadasa by the years allotted to the Antardasa planet. This product is then divided by 120. The quotient represents the years of the Antardasa. The remainder is multiplied by 12 and divided by 120 to get the months. Any subsequent remainder is multiplied by 30 and divided by 120 to get the days. This process applies recursively for further sub-divisions.",
